==Latin==

===Etymology===
From the end of the poem ''Odes'' I.11 by [[Horace]], ancient Roman poet.

:Sapiās, vīna liquēs, et spatio brevī<br>
:spem longam resecēs. Dum loquimur, fūgerit invidā<br>
:aetās. '''Carpe diem''' quam minimum crēdula posterō.

:Be wise, make wine, and in a short time,<br>
:lose any great hope. As we speak, time is cruelly slipping away.<br>
:'''Enjoy the day''', believing the least in the future.

